8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1257, L.D. 1886, “An Act Regarding
10 Penalties for Violation of the Law Governing Distracted Driving When the Violation
11 Results in the Death or Significant Injury of Another Person”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Include Serious Bodily Injury in the Law Governing Motor Vehicle
14 Violations Resulting in Death'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 29-A MRSA §2413-A, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 182, §1, is amended to
18 read:
19 §2413-A. Motor vehicle violation resulting in death or serious bodily injury
20 1. Offense. A person commits the civil violation of motor vehicle violation resulting
21 in death or serious bodily injury if that person, while operating a motor vehicle and
22 committing a traffic infraction, causes the death or serious bodily injury of another person.
23 2. Pleading and proof. The State must prove that the defendant's committing a traffic
24 infraction while operating a motor vehicle caused the death or serious bodily injury under
25 subsection 1. The court shall apply Title 17‑A, section 33 in assessing any causation under
26 this section.
27 3. Penalties. A person who violates this section commits a civil violation for which a
28 fine of not more than $5,000 may be adjudged. Any portion of the fine adjudged may be
29 satisfied by a court-ordered requirement of community service work. The court shall also
30 impose a license suspension of no less than 14 days and up to 4 years.
31 4. Definition. As used in this section, "serious bodily injury" has the same meaning
32 as in Title 17-A, section 2, subsection 23.'
33 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
34 number to read consecutively.
