COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1257, L.D. 1886
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
33 changes the title. The amendment amends the provision of law related to penalties
44 applicable when a person commits a motor vehicle violation that results in the death of
55 another person to provide that those penalties also apply to a person who commits a motor
66 vehicle violation that results in serious bodily injury to another person.
